en_148783_0	Ten fishermen who went fishing in the Northern Province has gone missing, Jaffna District Secretary N. Vedanayagam said.
en_148783_1	He said the group went missing yesterday.
en_148783_2	Meanwhile, an Indian fishing boat carrying six fishermen was swept to the Sri Lankan waters due to the adverse weather conditions in sea yesterday.
en_148783_3	They were taken into Jaffna police custody.
en_148783_4	Fishermen were advised not to go to sea today due to the prevailing bad weather.
